    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_færdyg" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>færdyg</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>færdug</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>самоцвет</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>gem</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>драгоценный камень</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>jewel</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>бусинка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>bead</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>færdgutæ</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>бусы</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>beads</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>ожерелье</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>necklace</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">ср.</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">cf.</note>
                        <quote>cykūrajy færdyg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>чудесный камень-самоцвет, доставляющий его обладателю счастье</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a wonderful gemstone that brings happiness to its owner</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_Коста._Этн."
                            /><biblScope>11–12</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_Коста._Этн."
                            /><biblScope>11–12</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ūrs dony bylyl saw færdyg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на берегу белой речки черный самоцвет</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>black gem on the banks of the white river</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>196</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pardu-ka</w></mentioned>, где <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pardu-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">первоначально —</note>
                        <gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>яркий</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pṛdāku-</w>
                        <gloss><q>змея</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>тигр</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>пантера</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">буквально</note>
                        <gloss><q>пестрое (животное)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Сюда же <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pul</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %i*pṛd-%i, как %igul%i
                            ‘роза’ из %i*vrd-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>монета (‘блестящая’)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>рыбья чешуя</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>palāā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из
                            %i*pardākā%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>цветы</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>флаг</q></gloss></mentioned> (последнее слово связывают с
                    пракритским %ipaṭākā%i, — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"
                            /><biblScope>XV 112</biblScope></bibl>). Древности названия отвечает
                    древность предмета. Бусы как украшение обычны в сарматский период. „Рядовое
                    население украшало свой костюм бусами и бисером. Обычай этот был широко
                    распространен у сармат и появился на Кубани с проникновением сюда новых
                    сарматских племен“ (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Н. %sАнфимов%s. Древние
                            поселения Прикубанья. Краснодар, 1953, стр. 66</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">N. %sAnfimov%s. Ancient settlements of the Kuban region.
                            Krasnodar, 1953, p. 66</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Probably, traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pardu-ka</w></mentioned>, where <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pardu-</w><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">initially meant</note>
                        <gloss><q>multicoloured</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bright</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pṛdāku-</w>
                        <gloss><q>snake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>tiger</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>panther</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w/><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">literally</note>
                        <gloss><q>multicoloured (animal)</q></gloss></mentioned>. See also
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pul</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                            %i*pṛd-%i, as %igul%i ‘rose’ is from %i*vrd-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>coin (‘shiny’)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fish-scale</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>palāā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                            %i*pardākā%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>flowers</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>флаг</q></gloss></mentioned> (some people relate the latter word
                    to Eteocretan %ipaṭākā%i, — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"
                            /><biblScope>XV 112</biblScope></bibl>). The antiquity of the name
                    corresponds to the antiquity of the object. Beads as decoration are common in
                    the Sarmatian period. “The ordinary population decorated their costume with
                    beads. This custom was widespread among the Sarmatians and appeared in the Kuban
                    with the penetration of new Sarmatian tribes here“ (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="en">N. %sAnfimov%s.
                            Ancient settlements of the Kuban region. Krasnodar, 1953, p.
                            66</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
            </entry>
